The course is made of three sections where each section concentrates on one game engine: Unity, Godot and Unreal Engine 4. The students will practise their knowledge by making a small game prototype in each engine.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course teaches to use the three common game engines: Unity, Godot and Unreal Engine 4. Students will learn to build their game architectures in each engine and will know which engine is the most fitting for solving a certian problem.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After taking the course the student: - Has aquired the fundamental knowledge to use Unity, Godot and Unreal Engine 4 game engines. - Is capable of using these engines to program a game. - Knows the architecure patterns of these engines and is capable of using them. - Is capable of comparing these engines in terms of suitability for solving a specific problem.
